---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../components/primitives/SectionHeader.astro';
import Win from '../components/primitives/Win.astro';
import { author } from '../config/author';
---
<BaseLayout title="privacy" description="Privacy policy for joaoaleixo.com — short version: I don't collect anything.">
  <div class="page-enter privacy">
    <SectionHeader
      kicker="// cat ./privacy.md"
      num="07"
      title="privacy"
      subtitle="short version: I don't collect anything."
    />

    <Win title="privacy.md" hasFooter>
      <div slot="footer">
        <span>last reviewed · {new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10)}</span>
        <span>tl;dr — no cookies, no analytics</span>
      </div>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          This page is about keeping things straightforward and making sure you know how
          your privacy is handled on this site. Anything below applies to
          <strong>joaoaleixo.com</strong>. Questions or concerns? Drop me a line at
          <a href={`mailto:${author.email}`}>{author.email}</a>.
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>The content on this site is my personal take on things. Unless stated otherwise, it doesn't reflect the views of anyone else I might be associated with.</li>
          <li>I'm not liable for issues caused by third-party services linked to from here.</li>
          <li>These policies apply to every page under this domain.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>// the promise</h2>
        <p>
          Here, you're more than a visitor — you're a guest. I don't collect personal
          information about you. I don't have it, don't want it, can't lose it.
        </p>
        <p>
          There's no analytics script. No advertising. No tracking pixels. No newsletter
          signup quietly doubling as a mailing list. The site is static HTML, shipped to
          your browser and that's it.
        </p>

        <h2>// first party</h2>
        <p>
          I don't set any cookies or local-storage keys for tracking. The only things
          this site stores locally — in <code>localStorage</code>, on your device,
          never transmitted — are your visual preferences (accent colour, theme,
          scanlines, font pairing) so the site looks the way you left it next time.
          Clear your site data and they're gone.
        </p>

        <h2>// third party</h2>
        <p>
          I lean on a couple of services to get the site in front of you. Here's the list:
        </p>

        <h3>Hosting / CDN</h3>
        <p>
          This site is deployed as a static bundle and served through a CDN. The hosting
          provider may collect request-level data (IP address, user agent, request path)
          for operational reasons — rate limits, abuse prevention, basic error logs.
          I don't have access to aggregated visitor reports.
        </p>

        <h3>Google Fonts</h3>
        <p>
          Fonts are loaded from Google Fonts. Your browser fetches font files directly
          from their servers, which means Google may collect usage data. See their
          <a href="https://developers.google.com/fonts/faq/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy FAQ</a>
          for details. If this bothers you, the site degrades gracefully to system
          monospace fonts.
        </p>

        <h3>Outbound links</h3>
        <p>
          Some pages link out to GitHub, LinkedIn, Stack Overflow, and similar. Those
          sites have their own privacy practices — your controls are in your hands
          once you leave here.
        </p>

        <h2>// the bigger picture</h2>
        <p>
          I aim to minimize tracking to effectively zero, but the broader web still
          tracks in ways I don't fully control (CDN logs, browser fingerprinting, ISPs).
          Use an ad blocker. Use a browser that respects you. Use DNS-level filtering
          if you want belt-and-braces. You probably already do.
        </p>

        <p class="sig">— João</p>
      </div>
    </Win>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .privacy { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; }
  .prose {
    font-family: var(--mono-body);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    max-width: 72ch;
  }
  .prose p { margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .prose strong { color: var(--ink); }
  .prose ul { margin: 0 0 16px; padding-left: 18px; }
  .prose ul li { padding: 2px 0; }
  .prose code {
    font-family: var(--mono-ui);
    font-size: 12.5px;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    background: var(--panel-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
    border-radius: 2px;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .prose h2 {
    font-family: var(--mono-display);
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 28px 0 10px;
    letter-spacing: .02em;
  }
  .prose h3 {
    font-family: var(--mono-ui);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--ink);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: .14em;
    margin: 18px 0 6px;
  }
  .prose a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed color-mix(in oklab, var(--accent) 40%, var(--line));
  }
  .prose a:hover { border-bottom-style: solid; }
  .sig {
    margin-top: 28px !important;
    padding-top: 14px;
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--line);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
  }
</style>
